Phase 1: Setup & Keyword Discovery
Goal: Understand what users are actually searching for.
Tool: Google Trends
Activity: Compare two related terms (e.g., "Cyber Security Course" vs.
"Ethical Hacking Training").
Task: Identify which term has higher interest in your specific region
over the last 12 months.
Tool: AnswerThePublic
Activity: Enter a "seed" keyword related to the chosen website.
Task: Students must find 3 "Question" keywords (Starting with Who,
What, Why) that the website should answer to rank better.
Phase 2: On-Page SEO Audit
Goal: Analyze how search engines "see" the page content.
1. Tool: SEO Quake
(Chrome Extension)
Task: Run a "Diagnosis" on the homepage.
Checklist: Is the Title Tag under 60 characters?
Is there a Meta Description? (If not, students must write one).
2. Tool: Google PageSpeed Insights
Activity: Analyze the mobile vs. desktop performance.
Task: Note the Core Web Vitals score and list two specific images that need
compression to improve speed.
Phase 3: Off-Page & Authority Check
Goal: Measure the website's "reputation" on the web.
Tool: Ahrefs Backlink Checker
(Free version)
Activity: Enter the URL to see the Domain Rating (DR) and number
of backlinks.
Task: Identify the "Top 5" referring domains. Are they high-quality
educational/news sites or low-quality directories?
Tool: Moz Link Explorer
Activity: Check the Spam Score.
Task: Discuss why a high spam score (over 10%) is dangerous for a
website's health.
